Review Comment:
   It's mostly an artifact of code history…we have this table in the spec: https://arrow.apache.org/docs/format/Flight.html#error-handling and not all codes mapped cleanly to an existing C++ status so a mix of Status and FlightStatusDetail is used. But for transports, I wanted to force them to map to and from the "abstract" error codes instead of ad-hoc mapping to Arrow/gRPC statuses, hence TransportStatus. Those do feel rather redundant.
   
   I could probably rework this to just work with Status/FlightStatusDetail then, and accept some messiness when re-mapping it to/from gRPC/UCX?

